<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=8928'><h3>View taxon page for Berberis</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#JX1'">1.</a><a name="JX1."> </a> Leaves simple

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#JX2'">2.</a><a name="JX2."> </a> Leaves evergreen, with 6&ndash;8 coarse, generally terminal spines; petals orange <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15578">.....&nbsp;B. darwinii</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#JX2.">2'</a><a name="JX2'"> </a> Leaves deciduous, with >> 8, small, marginal spines; petals yellow <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15584">.....&nbsp;B. vulgaris</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#JX1.">1'</a><a name="JX1'"> </a> Leaves compound

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#JX3'">3.</a><a name="JX3."> </a> Bud scales persistent among upper leaves, 15&ndash;45 mm, thick, lanceolate; leaflets &plusmn; palmately veined <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15594">.....&nbsp;B. nervosa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#JX3.">3'</a><a name="JX3'"> </a> Bud scales generally deciduous, &lt; 5 mm, thin, ovate to deltate; leaflets generally pinnately veined

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#JX4'">4.</a><a name="JX4."> </a> Inflorescence open, flowers generally &lt; 10; petiole generally &lt; 2 cm; terminal leaflets generally lanceolate, oblong, or narrowly elliptic &mdash; Southwestern California, D

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#JX5'">5.</a><a name="JX5."> </a> Leaflets generally 3, terminal sessile <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15580">.....&nbsp;B. harrisoniana</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#JX5.">5'</a><a name="JX5'"> </a> Leaflets 3&ndash;9, terminal stalked

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#JX6'">6.</a><a name="JX6."> </a> Leaflets flat to &plusmn; wavy, not folded along midrib, serrate, spines generally > 8 per side, &plusmn; 1 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15595">.....&nbsp;B. nevinii</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#JX6.">6'</a><a name="JX6'"> </a> Leaflets wavy, generally folded along midrib, &plusmn; lobed, spines generally 3&ndash;8 per side, 1&ndash;4 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX7'">7.</a><a name="JX7."> </a> Terminal leaflet generally &lt; 2 &times; width; berries yellow-red when fresh, &plusmn; glaucous, not inflated <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15593">.....&nbsp;B. higginsiae</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX7.">7'</a><a name="JX7'"> </a> Terminal leaflet generally > 2 &times; width; berries blue-black when fresh, heavily glaucous, not inflated or inflated only due to insect parasitism

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#JX8'">8.</a><a name="JX8."> </a> Terminal leaflet generally lance-ovate, length generally &lt; 3 &times; width; flowers 8&ndash;12; fruit yellow- to purple-red <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15591">.....&nbsp;B. fremontii</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 42 ;"><a href="#JX8.">8'</a><a name="JX8'"> </a> Terminal leaflet generally narrow-lanceolate, length generally > 3 &times; width; flowers 3&ndash;5; fruit red-brown to dark purple <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15592">.....&nbsp;B. haematocarpa</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#JX4.">4'</a><a name="JX4'"> </a> Inflorescence dense, flowers > 10; petiole generally > 2 cm (0&ndash;3 cm in <I>Berberis pinnata</I>); terminal leaflets generally ovate to wide-elliptic

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#JX9'">9.</a><a name="JX9."> </a> Leaflet margin strongly wavy, thick, generally hard, spines 6&ndash;10(12) per side, 2&ndash;5 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=76967">.....&nbsp;B. aquifolium var. dictyota</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#JX9.">9'</a><a name="JX9'"> </a> Leaflet margin wavy to flat, &plusmn; thin, not hard, spines generally > 10 per side (to 0 in <I>Berberis pinnata</I>), 1&ndash;2 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#JX10'">10.</a><a name="JX10."> </a> Petioles generally > 3 cm; leaflets generally 5&ndash;9

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX11'">11.</a><a name="JX11."> </a> Stems ascending to erect, generally 1&ndash;2 m; leaflets generally shiny adaxially <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=71483">.....&nbsp;B. aquifolium var. aquifolium</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX11.">11'</a><a name="JX11'"> </a> Stems spreading to erect, generally &lt; 0.8 m; leaflets generally dull adaxially <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=55117">.....&nbsp;B. aquifolium var. repens</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 28 ;"><a href="#JX10.">10'</a><a name="JX10'"> </a> Petioles generally 1&ndash;3 cm; leaflets generally 7&ndash;11 <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=15596">.....&nbsp;B. pinnata</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX12'">12.</a><a name="JX12."> </a> Leaflet margins generally flat, spines generally &lt; 1 mm; upper stems reclining to weakly erect; plant 2&ndash;4 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=49426">.....&nbsp;subsp. insularis</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 35 ;"><a href="#JX12.">12'</a><a name="JX12'"> </a> Leaflet margins generally wavy, spines generally > 1 mm; upper stems generally erect; plant generally &lt; 2 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=70025">.....&nbsp;subsp. pinnata</a></blockquote><P>
